The paper discusses the application of natural language processing and active learning algorithms to solve software engineering problems, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of software engineering (cs.SE), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper specifically mentions identifying software security vulnerabilities (cs.CR) and test case prioritization (cs.LG) as potential software engineering tasks that could benefit from the total recall problem.
